<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910808-0001</DOCNO><DOCID>910808-0001.</DOCID><HL>   Technology:   ASK Computer Posts   Flat 4th-Period Net;   Sees 1st-Quarter Loss</HL><DATE>08/08/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   ASKI</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)SOFTWARE (SOF)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. -- ASK Computer Systems Inc.reported flat earnings for its fiscal fourth quarter endedJune 30, and predicted a loss for fiscal 1992's first period.   ASK, a maker of software for manufacturing plants andother businesses, acquired a large software database companylast year for $110 million. The acquisition swelledfourth-quarter revenue to $127.9 million from $66.5 million ayear ago. However, good will, debt and other costs associatedwith the acquisition kept net income at $2.6 million, or 13cents a share, compared with $2.6 million, or 19 cents, inthe year-earlier period. The most recent pershare figure islower because the company issued stock to help finance thepurchase of the database concern.</LP><TEXT>   Les Wright, ASK's executive vice president of finance andadministration, said revenues dip seasonally in the fiscalfirst quarter, and that earnings will continue to be dampedby acquisition-related costs. Therefore, he said, &quot;while itis difficult to predict the magnitude of the decline, weexpect that it will result in a net loss in the first quarterof fiscal 1992.&quot; The mean estimate of analysts was for abreak-even first quarter, according to Zacks InvestmentResearch Inc.   In the first quarter ended Sept. 30, 1990, ASK earned$711,000, or five cents a share, on revenue of $44.5 million.For all of fiscal 1991, the company reported net of $2.7million, or 15 cents a share, down sharply from $5 million,or 37 cents a share, in fiscal 1990. Fiscal 1991 revenue was$343.9 million, up from $207.5 million.   The company announced results after the close of tradingyesterday. Its stock finished at $8.625 a share, unchanged,in national over-the-counter trading.</TEXT></DOC>